{
  "stem": "19210.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 274.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think that I'm very happy, ultimately, that I was able to, to marry within my faith-- that's what I wanted-- and raise, raise Jewish children, which I did.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I became a tourist driver guide.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I drove the president of Israel, Isaac Ben-Zvi, to the excavations of Hatzor, H-A-T-Z-O-R, when they were excavating.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in Rosh Pina, I picked up a very famous person-- the-- at the time, was the chief of the staff of the Israeli army and also a leading archeologist [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] by the name of-- God, I have a mental block right now.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Give me a moment so my, my thoughts come back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we went to Hatzor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and I also drove.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No, I was an escort for President Chaim Weizmann to the kibbutz Yam during the Second Armistice, no.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was also an escort from the Haganah to another, another general [INAUDIBLE], General [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Drawer, ?] I believe, to the American kibbutz in Gesher HaZiv, the Bridge of Glory, that was named after these [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I drove a professor which was a guest of the government of Israel from Haifa to the King David in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many years later, I found out who the man was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I did not know his name at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But his name was Fritz [INAUDIBLE], who was the leading primary person to work on the discovery of aspirin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a Jewish man from Austria.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I was asked to-- because I spoke German-- to drive a German couple to, to Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when I came to pick them up at the Hotel Zion in Haifa, they were speaking Portuguese.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were speaking Brazilian.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
